# Number cell types with large FD of lin28a
la_jump <- t(apply(la_ct_mn, 1, function(x) {
    if (x[1] == -1) 
        x[1] <- x[2]
    res1 <- ifelse(x[1] == 0, (x[3] + 0.1)/(x[1] + 0.1), x[3]/x[1])
    mn1 <- x[1]
    mn2 <- x[3]
    res2 <- ifelse(min(mn1, mn2) < 0.1, log2((mn1 + 0.1)/(mn2 + 0.1)), 
        log2(mn1/mn2))  # same with cal_wilp2, not good
    res <- c(res1, res2)
    return(res)
}))
sapply(c(1/4, 1/3, 1/2), function(x) {
    sum(la_jump[, 1] <= x)
})

cal_fd_by_mn <- function(mn1, mn2, cut_mean = 0.5, low_comp = 0.1) {
    # if min < 0.1, then +.1
    data <- cbind(mn1, mn2)
    vmin <- apply(data, 1, min)
    vmax <- apply(data, 1, max)
    is_high <- vmax >= cut_mean
    data[vmin < low_comp, ] <- data[vmin < low_comp, ] + low_comp
    fd <- log2(data[, 2]/data[, 1])  # mn2 / mn1 !!!!
    fd[!is_high] <- 0  # set to 0 FD for low-expressed genes
    return(fd)
}
clu_temp_fd <- mapply(cal_fd_by_mn, mn1 = split(t(f1_st2_mn[[1]]), 1:ncol(f1_st2_mn[[1]])), 
    mn2 = split(t(f1_st2_mn[[2]]), 1:ncol(f1_st2_mn[[2]])), MoreArgs = list(cut_mean = 0.3))

# a function for enrichment test logic 2 and 4 use the same function
# but different gene set
test_enrich_logic2 <- function(diag, test, total) {
    y <- diag[diag %in% total]
    x <- test[test %in% total]
    test_mx <- matrix(c(sum(x %in% y), sum(x %in% setdiff(total, y)), sum(y %in% 
        setdiff(total, x)), sum(setdiff(total, x) %in% setdiff(total, y))), 
        nr = 2)
    pv <- fisher.test(test_mx)$p.value
    od <- fisher.test(test_mx)$estimate
    return(c(pv, sum(x %in% y), length(y), sum(x %in% y)/length(x), length(y)/length(total), 
        length(x), od))
}

# lin28a target
plot_enrich_tar <- function(mx, back, ratio, name, path = "../result/temporal/", 
    title = "", perc_col, wd = 7, adj = 25, lab_cex = 0.5, main_cex = 1) {
    # pdf(paste(path,name,'.pdf',sep='') ,height=5,width=wd)
    par(cex = 2, las = 1, mar = c(2, 4, 4, 0), lwd = 1, pch = 16)
    tmp <- barplot(mx, col = c("grey", "red"), ylab = "Number of genes", 
        main = title, names.arg = rep("", ncol(mx)), cex.main = main_cex)
    text(tmp, par("usr")[3] - (par("usr")[4] - par("usr")[3])/8, colnames(mx), 
        xpd = NA, cex = lab_cex)
    text(tmp, par("usr")[4] * 1.15, label = paste(round(ratio, 2), sep = ""), 
        xpd = NA, cex = 1, col = perc_col)
    # text( tmp, apply(mx,2,sum)+adj, label=apply(mx,2,sum), cex=.6,xpd=NA)
    text(par("usr")[1] - (par("usr")[2] - par("usr")[1])/8, par("usr")[4] * 
        1.15, label = round(back, 2), cex = 1, xpd = NA, col = "darkgrey")
    # dev.off()
}
